name: The Finger Beer Mats
description:
Only 2000 produced and distributed. 

40 remain untouched, unused, 
signed and numbered. 

Micah Purnell’s work for Notes from Nowhere (a group exhibition including Turner Prize Winner Douglas Gordon amongst other highly acclaimed artists) consists of a beer mat featuring a stylized hand. Entitled The Finger, five white graphic blocks against a blood red background portray the universally aggressive raised single finger hand gesture. Within this graphic rendition of aggression however, Purnell has written the biblical quote ‘Bless those who curse you’ creating a contemplative counterpoint to the card’s image.

The beer mats were be distributed across Frome’s many different pubs throughout the duration of the project creating a distinctive counterpoint to the normal alcohol promotion normally found on this form of advertising.

Useful Risograph Printing Information
Risograph is a soya-based eco-friendly ink and printing option. There are no waste inks, no fixers, no wash downs, no disposable aluminium plates. It uses very little energy as there is no heat involved.  While this method of printing leaves a chalky effect that can smudge to the touch, it has a lovely matt finish, unattainable by many other methods.
